### Pacific plate

The vast [Pacific plate](/Pacific_plate), in its millions of years of relentless motion, has traversed numerous hotspots, leaving behind a remarkable geological signature. For instance, its journey over the [Bowie hotspot](/Bowie_hotspot) has meticulously sculpted the [Kodiak–Bowie Seamount chain](/Kodiak-Bowie_Seamount_chain) across the expansive [Gulf of Alaska](/Gulf_of_Alaska), a trail of submerged mountains documenting its ancient path. This region is part of what some geologists refer to as the "[Hotspot highway](/Hotspot_highway)" in the south Pacific Ocean, a testament to the sheer number and activity of these deep-seated mantle anomalies.

